-- Winter Wheat in China Shows `Emerging Signs' of Drought, Ministry Reports
-- B y   S t a n l e y   J a m e s
-- 2010-11-10T02:15:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-10/winter-wheat-in-china-shows-emerging-signs-of-drought-ministry-reports.html
Winter wheat crops in northern and
eastern China have showed “emerging signs” of drought after
receiving below-average rain since planting, the Ministry of
Agriculture said, without elaborating. Regional authorities
should take measures to protect plants against the dry
conditions and possible freezing, according to a statement on
the ministry’s website dated yesterday.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stanley James at 
 sjames8@bloomberg.net  